{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:psalms.80",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 80,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 80 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:1",
      "text": "For the end, a Psalm for Asaph, concerning the wine-presses. - Rejoice ye in God our helper; shout aloud to the God of Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:2",
      "text": "Take a psalm, and produce the timbrel, the pleasant psaltery with the harp.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:3",
      "text": "Blow the trumpet at the new moon, in the glorious day of your feast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:4",
      "text": "For this is an ordinance for Israel, and a statute of the God of Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:5",
      "text": "He made it to be a testimony in Joseph, when he came forth out of the land of Egypt: he heard a language which he understood not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:6",
      "text": "He removed his back from burdens: his hands slaved in making the baskets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:7",
      "text": "Thou didst call upon me in trouble, and I delivered thee; I heard thee in the secret place of the storm: I proved thee at the water of Strife. Pause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:8",
      "text": "Hear, my people, and I will speak to thee, O Israel; and I will testify to thee: if thou wilt hearken to me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:9",
      "text": "there shall be no new god in thee; neither shalt thou worship a strange god.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:10",
      "text": "For I am the Lord thy God, that brought thee out of the land of Egypt: open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:11",
      "text": "But my people hearkened not to my voice; and Israel gave no heed to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:12",
      "text": "So I let them go after the ways of their own hearts: they will go on in their own ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:13",
      "text": "If my people had hearkened to me, if Israel had walked in my ways,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:14",
      "text": "I should have put down their enemies very quickly, and should have laid my hand upon those that afflicted them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:15",
      "text": "The Lord’s enemies should have lied to him: but their time shall be for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.80.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:16",
      "text": "And he fed them with the fat of wheat; and satisfied them with honey out of the rock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
